The NL approaches utilized in this study were resolved with the Levenbergy-Marquardt iteration algorithm in Originlab Pro 2018. This regression generally comprises of the minimization or maximization of the distribution error between the predicted and experimental data, based on the convergence conditions. The error functions applied are the NL chi-square (X2) error, the residual sum of squares error (RSS) and root mean square error (RMSE) which are assessed using Eq. (4–5), where qcal is the calculated (modelled), qexp is the experimental data and N is the number of data points49,50.4\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
