				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\mathbf{N}} = 2^{K} + 2K + C = 2^{3} + 2.3 + 6 = 20$$\end{document}where K is the number of factors to be examined, C is the number of experiments carried out at the centre, and N is the number of runs. Table S1 displays the lowest and upper bounds for each factor. Analysis of variance (ANOVA) was used to statistically analyse the resulting model. Surface contour plots were utilised to investigate the relationships between the variables.

